-uniform","title":"School uniform","description":"Schools set school uniform policy and must make their uniform policy. You should talk to the school if you think your child is being discriminated against.","isStepByStep":false,"popular":false},{"url":"https://www.gov.uk/free-school-transport","title":"Free school transport","description":"Free transport from your local council - eligibility, rules for children with special educational needs and disabilities (SEND), how to apply","isStepByStep":false,"popular":false},{"url":"https://www.gov.uk/school-attendance-absence","title":"School attendance and absence","description":"You can be prosecuted if your child has unauthorised absence from school - truancy, help with getting your child to school, and legal action to enforce school attendance","isStepByStep":false,"popular":true},{"url":"https://www.gov.uk/national-curriculum","title":"The national curriculum","description":"The English national curriculum means children in different schools (at primary and secondary level) study the same subjects to similar standards - it's split into key stages with tests","isStepByStep":false,"popular":false},{"url":"https://www.gov.uk/complain-about-school","title":"Complain about a school","description":"Complain about a school - complaints process, when to complain to the Department for Education, the Education Funding Agency or Ofsted.","isStepByStep":false,"popular":false},{"url":"https://www.gov.uk/childcare-calculator","title":"Check what help you could get with childcare costs","description":"Check what help you might be able to get with childcare schemes like tax credits, Tax-Free Childcare, childcare vouchers and free childcare or education for 2 to 4-year-olds. ","isStepByStep":false,"popular":false},{"url":"https://www.gov.uk/parental-leave","title":"Unpaid parental leave","description":"Employer and employee guide to unpaid parental leave - eligibility, how much leave can be taken and notice periods, postponing leave",